1
00:00:06,883 --> 00:00:08,885
(LIQUID SQUIRTING)

2
00:00:23,274 --> 00:00:25,276
(FLIES BUZZING)

3
00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:37,121
SOLDIER: It's time to go.

4
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:40,541
Did you hear me?

5
00:00:41,834 --> 00:00:43,628
This is an evacuation. You understand?

6
00:00:45,213 --> 00:00:46,339
You have to come with me.

7
00:00:47,131 --> 00:00:48,132
Why?

8
00:00:48,966 --> 00:00:50,760
Because they told me,
so now I'm telling you.

9
00:00:52,095 --> 00:00:53,721
Everyone in this village, everyone.

10
00:00:54,722 --> 00:00:56,516
It's not safe here.
There's radiation in the air.

11
00:00:56,599 --> 00:00:57,600
What's wrong with you?

12
00:00:58,684 --> 00:01:00,061
Do you know how old I am?

13
00:01:01,896 --> 00:01:03,940
I don't know. Old.

14
00:01:05,024 --> 00:01:06,025
I'm 82.

15
00:01:07,235 --> 00:01:08,861
I've lived here my whole life.

16
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:12,448
Right here, that house, this place.

17
00:01:13,407 --> 00:01:15,326
What do I care about safe?

18
00:01:17,161 --> 00:01:18,204
SOLDIER: I have a job.

19
00:01:18,996 --> 00:01:19,997
Don't cause trouble.

20
00:01:20,832 --> 00:01:21,833
WOMAN: Trouble?

21
00:01:23,167 --> 00:01:26,003
You're not the first soldier
to stand here with a gun.

22
00:01:27,088 --> 00:01:29,465
When I was 12, the revolution came.

23
00:01:30,341 --> 00:01:32,969
Czar's men. Then Bolsheviks.

24
00:01:33,761 --> 00:01:35,930
Boys like you marching in lines.

25
00:01:36,639 --> 00:01:38,808
They told us to leave. No.

26
00:01:39,892 --> 00:01:41,978
Then there was Stalin and his famine,

27
00:01:42,645 --> 00:01:43,771
the Holodomor.

28
00:01:44,814 --> 00:01:48,025
My parents died.
Two of my sisters died.

29
00:01:48,901 --> 00:01:50,820
They told the rest of us to leave.

30
00:01:51,654 --> 00:01:52,655
No.

31
00:01:53,281 --> 00:01:54,740
Then the Great War.

32
00:01:55,616 --> 00:01:57,743
German boys. Russian boys.

33
00:01:58,536 --> 00:02:01,747
More soldiers,
more famine, more bodies.

34
00:02:03,207 --> 00:02:04,876
My brothers never came home.

35
00:02:06,085 --> 00:02:08,296
But I stayed, and I'm still here.

36
00:02:09,380 --> 00:02:11,299
After all that I have seen,

37
00:02:12,925 --> 00:02:14,468
so I should leave now,

38
00:02:14,886 --> 00:02:17,263
because of something
I cannot see at all?

39
00:02:18,389 --> 00:02:19,390
No.

40
00:02:32,904 --> 00:02:33,905
(HORN HONKING)

41
00:02:35,198 --> 00:02:36,199
Just one moment!

42
00:02:46,209 --> 00:02:47,210
It's time to go.

43
00:02:54,258 --> 00:02:56,010
SOLDIER: (SIGHS)
Please stand up now.

44
00:02:57,386 --> 00:02:58,721
(MILK SQUIRTING)

45
00:03:05,144 --> 00:03:06,145
(GUN COCKS)

46
00:03:07,188 --> 00:03:08,356
This is your last warning.

47
00:03:15,363 --> 00:03:16,364
(GUNSHOT)

48
00:03:16,906 --> 00:03:17,907
(THUD)

49
00:03:25,581 --> 00:03:26,624
It's time to go.

50
00:03:36,425 --> 00:03:38,344
(FLIES BUZZING)

51
00:04:34,442 --> 00:04:35,526
(KEYS JANGLING)

52
00:04:40,865 --> 00:04:41,866
Come on.

53
00:05:32,792 --> 00:05:36,379
(RADIATION DETECTOR CLICKING)

54
00:05:40,341 --> 00:05:42,510
(CLICKING CONTINUES)

55
00:05:46,138 --> 00:05:47,139
MAN 1: Point four.

56
00:05:59,068 --> 00:06:00,069
MAN 2: Point six.

57
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:07,201
MAN 3: Fifteen.

58
00:06:07,284 --> 00:06:09,370
(DETECTOR CRACKLING)

59
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:13,582
(CRACKLING CONTINUES)

60
00:06:23,634 --> 00:06:25,594
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

61
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:47,032
(HELICOPTER HOVERING IN DISTANCE)

62
00:06:55,958 --> 00:06:56,959
(EXHALES)

63
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,672
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

64
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:06,093
Legasov.

65
00:07:06,510 --> 00:07:07,511
(INDISTINCT TALKING OVER PHONE)

66
00:07:08,721 --> 00:07:09,722
I'll meet him there.

67
00:07:59,563 --> 00:08:00,564
(INAUDIBLE CONVERSATION)

68
00:08:09,031 --> 00:08:10,783
LEGASOV: The atom
Is a humbling thing.

69
00:08:13,285 --> 00:08:15,162
It's not humbling, it's humiliating.

70
00:08:17,373 --> 00:08:18,999
Why is the core still exposed
to the air?

71
00:08:19,083 --> 00:08:20,668
Why have we not already covered it up?

72
00:08:21,252 --> 00:08:24,588
We want to,
but we can't get close enough.

73
00:08:25,339 --> 00:08:28,551
The debris on the roof is graphite
from the core itself.

74
00:08:29,301 --> 00:08:32,846
Until we can push it off the roof
back into the reactor,

75
00:08:33,222 --> 00:08:35,182
it'll kill anyone who gets near it.

76
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:39,645
You can see
the roof is in three levels.

77
00:08:40,062 --> 00:08:42,606
We've named them.
The small one here is Katya.

78
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:45,150
1,000 roentgen per hour.

79
00:08:45,568 --> 00:08:48,237
Presume two hours of exposure
is fatal.

80
00:08:48,445 --> 00:08:49,989
The one on the side, Nina.

81
00:08:50,239 --> 00:08:52,408
2,000 roentgen. One hour, fatal.

82
00:08:52,491 --> 00:08:55,536
We used remote-control bulldozers
in Afghanistan.

83
00:08:55,619 --> 00:08:57,913
Too heavy. They'd fall right through.

84
00:08:58,914 --> 00:08:59,915
So then...

85
00:09:00,499 --> 00:09:01,667
Moon rovers.

86
00:09:02,543 --> 00:09:04,545
Lunokhod STR-1's. They're light.

87
00:09:04,628 --> 00:09:07,298
And if we line them with lead,
they can withstand the radiation.

88
00:09:07,590 --> 00:09:09,049
SHCHERBINA:
We couldn't put a man on the moon.

89
00:09:09,758 --> 00:09:11,844
At least we can keep a man off a roof.

90
00:09:12,177 --> 00:09:14,346
That is the most
important thing, General.

91
00:09:14,430 --> 00:09:17,266
Under no circumstances
can men go up there.

92
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:19,184
Robots only.

93
00:09:20,227 --> 00:09:21,979
What about this large section here?

94
00:09:23,606 --> 00:09:24,607
Masha.

95
00:09:26,108 --> 00:09:27,610
12,000 roentgen.

96
00:09:29,695 --> 00:09:31,697
If you were to stand there
in full protective gear

97
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:33,532
head-to-toe for two minutes,

98
00:09:33,616 --> 00:09:35,409
your life expectancy
would be cut in half.

99
00:09:35,492 --> 00:09:37,620
By three minutes,
you're dead within months.

100
00:09:38,078 --> 00:09:40,789
Even our lunar rovers
won't work on Masha.

101
00:09:41,123 --> 00:09:44,084
That amount of gamma radiation
penetrates everything.

102
00:09:44,501 --> 00:09:48,005
The particles literally shred
the circuits in microchips apart.

103
00:09:48,255 --> 00:09:50,382
If it's more complicated
than a light switch,

104
00:09:50,799 --> 00:09:52,176
Masha will destroy it.

105
00:09:52,468 --> 00:09:53,844
It would be fair to say that

106
00:09:53,927 --> 00:09:56,639
that piece of roof
is the most dangerous place on Earth.

107
00:10:03,228 --> 00:10:05,773
So, what do we do?

108
00:10:09,026 --> 00:10:10,736
That's what we wanted to ask you.

109
00:10:50,109 --> 00:10:51,652
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

110
00:11:29,064 --> 00:11:31,066
(MEN COUGHING)

111
00:11:42,953 --> 00:11:44,204
(MEN LAUGHING)

112
00:11:44,288 --> 00:11:45,748
(SINGING INDISTINCTLY)

113
00:11:59,011 --> 00:12:01,013
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

114
00:12:24,578 --> 00:12:25,579
(DOOR CLOSES)

115
00:12:28,457 --> 00:12:30,042
Tent 1817

116
00:12:33,462 --> 00:12:34,463
(EXHALES)

117
00:12:44,973 --> 00:12:46,391
It's all right. It's free.

118
00:12:47,684 --> 00:12:48,811
It's a little early.

119
00:12:52,773 --> 00:12:53,774
(GRUNTS)

120
00:13:02,449 --> 00:13:03,450
Bacho.

121
00:13:05,828 --> 00:13:06,829
Pavel.

122
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:09,414
-Yeah?
-Mmm.

123
00:13:14,378 --> 00:13:15,587
What unit were you in?

124
00:13:16,713 --> 00:13:19,466
They had me in motor pool in Kiev,
but then they...

125
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:22,678
Not this bullshit. In Afghanistan.

126
00:13:22,761 --> 00:13:24,137
Oh. Oh, am...

127
00:13:24,221 --> 00:13:25,889
I wasn't in Afghanistan.

128
00:13:28,851 --> 00:13:29,852
I'm not in the military.

129
00:13:32,229 --> 00:13:33,230
(SIGHS WEARILY)

130
00:13:34,022 --> 00:13:35,023
They're running out of men.

131
00:13:47,119 --> 00:13:48,453
Showers. Food.

132
00:13:49,037 --> 00:13:51,206
Those guys, they dig up the ground.

133
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:53,208
Those guys, they cut down trees.

134
00:13:54,376 --> 00:13:58,797
Those guys, they evacuate people,
I think, like villagers.

135
00:14:00,716 --> 00:14:01,717
What about them?

136
00:14:02,968 --> 00:14:04,428
I don't know them. Fuck them.

137
00:14:06,930 --> 00:14:07,931
Janek!

138
00:14:09,850 --> 00:14:12,311
-What do you want?
-Give me an egg basket.

139
00:14:12,519 --> 00:14:14,771
-No. I've only got the one...
-Give me the fucking basket!

140
00:14:18,942 --> 00:14:22,529
He's with me. You understand?
Nobody fucks with him.

141
00:14:25,490 --> 00:14:27,117
We make these from lead scrap.

142
00:14:27,576 --> 00:14:29,828
-Put it on under your balls.
-Now?

143
00:14:30,245 --> 00:14:32,664
No, no. You can wait
until the radiation gives you a cunt.

144
00:14:33,290 --> 00:14:34,416
Yes, now.

145
00:14:36,585 --> 00:14:39,129
Over your clothes. Fucking shit.

146
00:14:47,763 --> 00:14:49,598
-You ever go hunting?
-No.

147
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:53,769
Well, today's your lucky day.

148
00:14:54,811 --> 00:14:59,066
You, me, that ugly Armenian
in the tent, Garo,

149
00:14:59,232 --> 00:15:00,442
we do animal control.

150
00:15:01,818 --> 00:15:02,945
Animal control?

151
00:15:03,403 --> 00:15:06,323
Yeah, they're radioactive,
so they have to go.

152
00:15:07,866 --> 00:15:09,368
But it's not hard.
They're mostly pets.

153
00:15:10,243 --> 00:15:12,955
They're happy to see you.
They run right up to you.

154
00:15:13,455 --> 00:15:14,456
Bang!

155
00:15:14,539 --> 00:15:16,041
You load the bodies on a truck,

156
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:18,543
dump them in a pit,
bury them in concrete,

157
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:19,711
and then we drink.

158
00:15:20,587 --> 00:15:22,047
As much vodka as you want,

159
00:15:23,173 --> 00:15:24,257
plus 1,000 rubles.

160
00:15:26,969 --> 00:15:28,136
Let's go get you a gun.

161
00:15:56,915 --> 00:15:57,916
(DOOR BUZZES)

162
00:16:37,748 --> 00:16:38,749
Yes?

163
00:16:39,207 --> 00:16:42,377
I need to see the following documents.
They're listed as "permission only."

164
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:50,010
I'm working for the Central Committee.

165
00:17:03,106 --> 00:17:04,107
Comrade?

166
00:17:09,780 --> 00:17:10,781
(DOOR OPENS)

167
00:17:23,543 --> 00:17:25,087
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

168
00:17:37,599 --> 00:17:38,600
(DOOR OPENS)

169
00:17:42,813 --> 00:17:43,939
MAN: She can have that one.

170
00:17:51,571 --> 00:17:52,823
(DOOR CLOSES)

171
00:17:52,906 --> 00:17:53,949
Thank you, Comrade.

172
00:19:33,131 --> 00:19:35,258
MAN: (OVER RADIO) All clear.
TARAKANOV: Bring up the cameras.

173
00:19:36,843 --> 00:19:37,844
(BUZZING)

174
00:19:41,348 --> 00:19:42,849
-Signal?
-MAN: Acceptable.

175
00:19:42,933 --> 00:19:44,559
Running on board diagnostics.

176
00:19:45,101 --> 00:19:46,686
TARAKANOV: Tell me when
we're ready to move it.

177
00:19:47,812 --> 00:19:50,148
To think that's what we put
on the moon.

178
00:19:52,442 --> 00:19:53,902
Well, not that one.

179
00:19:55,946 --> 00:19:57,405
I know not that one.

180
00:19:58,573 --> 00:20:00,533
TARAKANOV: This rover was in storage.
They can build two more.

181
00:20:01,284 --> 00:20:03,036
That should cover Nina and Katya.

182
00:20:04,621 --> 00:20:05,747
SHCHERBINA: And Masha?

183
00:20:06,248 --> 00:20:07,958
TARAKANOV: The Central Committee
have informed me

184
00:20:08,166 --> 00:20:10,961
that they may have found something
that could work up there.

185
00:20:11,127 --> 00:20:12,963
-From the outside.
-American?

186
00:20:13,964 --> 00:20:15,173
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY) Of course not.

187
00:20:15,966 --> 00:20:17,509
It's a German police robot.

188
00:20:18,301 --> 00:20:20,262
But West German,
SO, as you can imagine,

189
00:20:20,345 --> 00:20:22,389
that wasn't
an easy conversation to have.

190
00:20:22,931 --> 00:20:26,101
Diagnostics complete.
Ready to engage main power and motor.

191
00:20:27,352 --> 00:20:28,353
TARAKANOV: Begin.

192
00:20:34,526 --> 00:20:35,527
Can we move it?

193
00:20:37,654 --> 00:20:38,738
(CLICKS)

194
00:20:42,951 --> 00:20:43,952
(CHUCKLES)

195
00:20:48,832 --> 00:20:51,543
Valery, what's that? A smile?

196
00:20:53,461 --> 00:20:54,838
(LAUGHS)

197
00:21:05,307 --> 00:21:06,308
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

198
00:21:06,391 --> 00:21:07,392
(DOOR OPENS)

199
00:21:08,268 --> 00:21:09,269
(DOOR CLOSES)

200
00:21:10,854 --> 00:21:13,356
KHOMYUK: I see your condition
has improved, Comrade Dyatlov.

201
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:14,649
No. Leave.

202
00:21:22,866 --> 00:21:23,950
I need your help.

203
00:21:26,828 --> 00:21:29,122
(INHALES AND EXHALES SLOWLY)

204
00:21:32,584 --> 00:21:35,045
Akimov initiated AZ-5.

205
00:21:36,212 --> 00:21:38,548
-When you gave the order...
-Order? What order?

206
00:21:40,467 --> 00:21:43,386
Toptunov called it out,
Akimov pressed it.

207
00:21:44,637 --> 00:21:46,222
It was the only
good decision they made.

208
00:21:46,306 --> 00:21:47,307
Incompetent morons.

209
00:21:49,184 --> 00:21:51,728
Can you confirm
that the reactor exploded

210
00:21:51,811 --> 00:21:53,563
after they attempted to shut it down?

211
00:21:54,689 --> 00:21:56,608
How do I even know it exploded, huh?

212
00:22:18,088 --> 00:22:19,255
I found this in the state archive.

213
00:22:21,466 --> 00:22:23,093
Written in 1976.

214
00:22:23,843 --> 00:22:25,011
It's about the operation

215
00:22:25,095 --> 00:22:27,722
of RBMK reactors
under extreme conditions.

216
00:22:27,806 --> 00:22:28,807
So?

217
00:22:29,265 --> 00:22:31,309
The names of the authors
have been redacted,

218
00:22:31,768 --> 00:22:33,436
and two pages have been removed.

219
00:22:34,646 --> 00:22:37,482
Well, the State must protect
its secrets, Comrade.

220
00:22:38,108 --> 00:22:39,651
Do you dare suggest otherwise?

221
00:22:41,277 --> 00:22:42,612
They made a mistake.

222
00:22:44,989 --> 00:22:47,325
They didn't redact
the table of contents.

223
00:22:58,420 --> 00:23:00,046
The missing pages apparently refer

224
00:23:00,130 --> 00:23:03,675
to a positive void coefficient
and AZ-5.

225
00:23:04,926 --> 00:23:06,177
Does that mean anything to you?

226
00:23:06,261 --> 00:23:08,888
What are you after here?
Why are you asking me this?

227
00:23:08,972 --> 00:23:11,182
You worked with this reactor.
You know it better than I do.

228
00:23:11,266 --> 00:23:13,226
So everything's my fault, then?

229
00:23:14,394 --> 00:23:15,478
Is that what this is?

230
00:23:15,562 --> 00:23:18,565
I'm not here to blame you.
I'm here to find out what happened.

231
00:23:19,732 --> 00:23:21,025
And whether you realize it or not,

232
00:23:21,109 --> 00:23:23,194
I'm your best chance
to avoid a bullet.

233
00:23:25,989 --> 00:23:27,365
Can you help me or not?

234
00:23:36,833 --> 00:23:38,626
I have no idea
what would have gone here.

235
00:23:38,710 --> 00:23:41,629
Void coefficients
have nothing to do with AZ-5.

236
00:23:42,672 --> 00:23:44,007
There. Now you can go.

237
00:23:44,841 --> 00:23:47,010
-You're not even curious?
-What for?

238
00:23:48,970 --> 00:23:51,389
You think the right question
will get you the truth?

239
00:23:51,473 --> 00:23:52,474
(SCOFFS)

240
00:23:53,183 --> 00:23:54,559
There's no truth.

241
00:23:55,602 --> 00:23:58,396
Ask the bosses whatever you want
and you'll get the lie.

242
00:23:59,898 --> 00:24:01,608
And I will get the bullet.

243
00:24:06,279 --> 00:24:07,280
(DOOR OPENS)

244
00:24:08,448 --> 00:24:09,449
(DOOR CLOSES)

245
00:25:09,884 --> 00:25:11,386
(GUN COCKING)

246
00:25:34,784 --> 00:25:36,202
I only have two rules.

247
00:25:36,786 --> 00:25:37,787
One.

248
00:25:38,746 --> 00:25:41,207
Don't point this gun at me.
That's easy, right?

249
00:25:41,916 --> 00:25:43,543
You can point it
at this piece of shit.

250
00:25:43,626 --> 00:25:45,295
I don't give a fuck. Never me.

251
00:25:46,754 --> 00:25:47,755
Two.

252
00:25:48,131 --> 00:25:51,009
If you hit an animal
and it doesn't die,

253
00:25:51,092 --> 00:25:52,802
keep shooting until it does.

254
00:25:54,137 --> 00:25:55,471
Don't let them suffer,

255
00:25:56,889 --> 00:25:58,891
or I'll kill you. Understand?

256
00:26:00,268 --> 00:26:01,269
I mean it.

257
00:26:02,812 --> 00:26:04,022
I've killed a lot of people.

258
00:26:09,777 --> 00:26:12,030
Good. Then we're ready.

259
00:26:20,413 --> 00:26:21,414
(GUN COCKS)

260
00:26:51,819 --> 00:26:54,822
Once we start, they'll run inside
where they feel safe.

261
00:26:55,948 --> 00:26:57,325
So we go door to door.

262
00:26:58,493 --> 00:26:59,494
Okay?

263
00:27:00,119 --> 00:27:01,120
Good.

264
00:27:03,873 --> 00:27:05,875
(WHISTLING)

265
00:27:08,002 --> 00:27:10,004
(DOGS BARKING)

266
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:17,178
(CONTINUES WHISTLING)

267
00:27:33,986 --> 00:27:34,987
(DOG WHIMPERS)

268
00:27:36,364 --> 00:27:37,365
(GUNS FIRING)

269
00:27:43,871 --> 00:27:44,872
(DOG YELPS)

270
00:27:47,458 --> 00:27:49,627
(DOGS BARKING)

271
00:27:51,629 --> 00:27:52,630
Hey!

272
00:27:53,297 --> 00:27:55,591
Do your job. Door to door.

273
00:28:10,648 --> 00:28:11,733
(DOG BARKING)

274
00:28:11,816 --> 00:28:12,817
(GUN FIRES)

275
00:28:33,045 --> 00:28:34,046
(GUN FIRES IN DISTANCE)

276
00:28:39,469 --> 00:28:42,180
-(DOG PANTING)
(GUNSHOT)

277
00:28:49,687 --> 00:28:51,647
Go. Go.

278
00:28:51,773 --> 00:28:53,733
Go away. Go!

279
00:29:01,491 --> 00:29:02,492
(BARKS)

280
00:29:06,078 --> 00:29:07,955
(DOG WHIMPERING)

281
00:29:16,339 --> 00:29:18,007
(WHIMPERING CONTINUES)

282
00:29:19,509 --> 00:29:20,510
(GUN FIRES IN DISTANCE)

283
00:29:37,235 --> 00:29:38,236
(GUNSHOT)

284
00:29:43,616 --> 00:29:44,951
(FLIES BUZZING)

285
00:29:47,537 --> 00:29:48,538
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

286
00:29:50,164 --> 00:29:51,624
Don't let them suffer.

287
00:29:52,250 --> 00:29:53,417
Sorry. Sorry.

288
00:29:56,546 --> 00:29:58,005
You're dragging that to the truck.

289
00:30:05,429 --> 00:30:06,430
(GUN FIRES IN DISTANCE)

290
00:30:13,563 --> 00:30:14,564
(DOG BARKS DISTANTLY)

291
00:30:26,784 --> 00:30:28,619
(FLIES BUZZING)

292
00:30:35,668 --> 00:30:36,752
You gonna eat?

293
00:30:47,722 --> 00:30:48,723
Drink.

294
00:30:52,768 --> 00:30:53,769
Again.

295
00:31:00,276 --> 00:31:01,277
(GULPS)

296
00:31:01,944 --> 00:31:02,945
(GRUNTS)

297
00:31:06,198 --> 00:31:07,199
Look...

298
00:31:09,994 --> 00:31:12,163
This happens to everyone
their first time.

299
00:31:13,289 --> 00:31:14,999
Normally when you kill a man.

300
00:31:17,084 --> 00:31:18,544
But for you, a dog.

301
00:31:19,003 --> 00:31:21,088
So what? There's no shame in it.

302
00:31:23,299 --> 00:31:25,217
You remember your first time, Garo?

303
00:31:26,218 --> 00:31:29,180
My first time, Afghanistan.

304
00:31:31,682 --> 00:31:33,434
We were moving through a house,

305
00:31:34,393 --> 00:31:37,563
and suddenly a man was there
and I shot him in the stomach.

306
00:31:39,857 --> 00:31:41,734
Yeah, that's a real war story.

307
00:31:43,235 --> 00:31:46,030
There are never any good stories
like in the movies. They're shit.

308
00:31:47,782 --> 00:31:51,077
A man was there, boom, stomach.

309
00:31:53,704 --> 00:31:55,748
I was so scared,
I didn't pull the trigger again

310
00:31:55,831 --> 00:31:57,249
for the rest of the day.

311
00:31:59,543 --> 00:32:02,129
I thought, "Well, that's it, Bacho.

312
00:32:03,839 --> 00:32:05,424
"You put a bullet in someone.

313
00:32:06,175 --> 00:32:07,885
"You're not you anymore.

314
00:32:08,552 --> 00:32:09,971
"You'll never be you again."

315
00:32:12,974 --> 00:32:16,310
But then you wake up the next morning,
and you're still you.

316
00:32:17,812 --> 00:32:18,980
And you realize

317
00:32:20,606 --> 00:32:22,066
that was you all along.

318
00:32:23,275 --> 00:32:24,735
You just didn't know.

319
00:32:35,454 --> 00:32:37,873
"The happiness of all mankind."

320
00:32:41,627 --> 00:32:42,628
What?

321
00:32:44,463 --> 00:32:47,174
"Our goal is the happiness
of all mankind."

322
00:32:48,592 --> 00:32:49,719
(SPITS)

323
00:32:55,016 --> 00:32:56,017
BACHO: Yeah.

324
00:33:01,063 --> 00:33:02,106
I'm happy.

325
00:33:02,815 --> 00:33:04,066
I'm happy every day.

326
00:33:06,485 --> 00:33:07,486
All right.

327
00:33:08,863 --> 00:33:09,947
Back to work.

328
00:33:11,198 --> 00:33:12,199
Come on.

329
00:33:26,881 --> 00:33:28,883
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

330
00:34:28,317 --> 00:34:29,318
(DOOR CLOSES)

331
00:34:31,028 --> 00:34:32,113
TARAKANOV: It's here.

332
00:35:01,475 --> 00:35:02,476
SOLDIER: All right.

333
00:35:04,687 --> 00:35:06,564
Get over. Right, hang on.

334
00:35:09,191 --> 00:35:10,734
Easy now. Careful.

335
00:35:11,735 --> 00:35:12,736
SOLDIER: Hold it!

336
00:35:21,287 --> 00:35:22,288
Joker.

337
00:35:23,998 --> 00:35:26,375
It's what the Germans
named it. "Joker."

338
00:35:26,625 --> 00:35:27,793
Is it ready?

339
00:35:28,460 --> 00:35:29,461
It's ready.

340
00:36:17,009 --> 00:36:18,010
MAN: Good signal.

341
00:36:19,470 --> 00:36:20,471
TARAKANOV: Cameras.

342
00:36:21,972 --> 00:36:22,973
Motors.

343
00:36:23,057 --> 00:36:24,058
(SWITCHES CLICKING)

344
00:36:25,351 --> 00:36:27,478
Motors, good. Signals, good.

345
00:36:28,604 --> 00:36:30,606
All right, let's take this easy.

346
00:36:31,190 --> 00:36:33,400
Forward one meter, reverse one meter.

347
00:36:35,694 --> 00:36:36,695
Forward one.

348
00:36:40,991 --> 00:36:42,284
Germans.

349
00:36:43,869 --> 00:36:44,995
Reverse one.

350
00:36:51,043 --> 00:36:52,044
(CLACKING)

351
00:36:55,297 --> 00:36:56,882
(CLACKING CONTINUES)

352
00:36:58,217 --> 00:36:59,218
Did you lose the signal?

353
00:37:05,266 --> 00:37:06,725
It's not the signal. It's the vehicle.

354
00:37:08,644 --> 00:37:09,728
It's dead.

355
00:37:16,235 --> 00:37:17,236
Shit.

356
00:37:20,447 --> 00:37:21,448
(DOOR OPENS)

357
00:37:22,241 --> 00:37:24,034
Of course, I know they're listening!

358
00:37:24,118 --> 00:37:26,245
I want them to hear!
I want them to hear it all!

359
00:37:26,704 --> 00:37:27,997
Do you know what we're doing here?

360
00:37:28,789 --> 00:37:30,833
Tell those idiots what they have done!

361
00:37:32,918 --> 00:37:34,586
I don't give a fuck!

362
00:37:36,422 --> 00:37:38,716
Tell them! Go tell them! Ryzhkov!

363
00:37:38,799 --> 00:37:40,009
Go tell them he's a joke!

364
00:37:40,092 --> 00:37:42,052
Tell fucking Gorbachev!

365
00:37:42,136 --> 00:37:43,137
Tell them!

366
00:38:06,618 --> 00:38:08,287
The official position of the State

367
00:38:09,288 --> 00:38:13,459
is that a global nuclear catastrophe
is not possible in the Soviet Union.

368
00:38:14,460 --> 00:38:15,461
They told the Germans

369
00:38:15,544 --> 00:38:20,174
that the highest detected level
of radiation was 2,000 roentgen.

370
00:38:22,134 --> 00:38:23,719
They gave them the propaganda number.

371
00:38:26,305 --> 00:38:28,265
That robot was never going to work.

372
00:38:32,936 --> 00:38:34,229
We need a new phone.

373
00:39:16,105 --> 00:39:17,648
What if we don't clear it?

374
00:39:18,232 --> 00:39:19,483
We have to clear it.

375
00:39:21,443 --> 00:39:24,196
If we don't clear the roof,
we can't build a cover over it.

376
00:39:26,532 --> 00:39:29,159
If we can't cover it,
that's 12,000 roentgen.

377
00:39:30,077 --> 00:39:33,497
Nearly twice the radiation
from the Hiroshima bomb.

378
00:39:34,498 --> 00:39:37,292
-Every hour, hour after hour...
-SHCHERBINA: I know, I know, I know.

379
00:39:38,127 --> 00:39:39,420
What about lead?

380
00:39:41,213 --> 00:39:42,548
We could... I don't know.

381
00:39:42,631 --> 00:39:45,884
We could melt it and pour it
from above, like a coating.

382
00:39:45,968 --> 00:39:47,428
TARAKANOV:
First of all, we've already used

383
00:39:47,511 --> 00:39:48,971
most of the lead we had...

384
00:39:49,054 --> 00:39:51,140
There's lead sheeting
around the instruments

385
00:39:51,223 --> 00:39:53,016
in the other reactor buildings.

386
00:39:53,225 --> 00:39:55,769
The soldiers are stripping it
for their armor.

387
00:39:55,853 --> 00:39:57,020
Are you serious?

388
00:39:59,064 --> 00:40:00,065
(SCOFFS)

389
00:40:00,149 --> 00:40:04,445
Even if, we're still talking
about boiling metal in a helicopter.

390
00:40:04,736 --> 00:40:06,905
And it's lead, Boris.
It'll weigh a ton.

391
00:40:09,658 --> 00:40:12,870
What if we shoot the graphite
into the hole?

392
00:40:13,454 --> 00:40:15,831
We've got high-caliber bullets,
exploding bullets.

393
00:40:15,914 --> 00:40:18,000
They wouldn't just ricochet,
they'd push...

394
00:40:18,083 --> 00:40:22,212
You wanna shoot exploding bullets
at an exposed nuclear reactor?

395
00:40:22,296 --> 00:40:23,881
-Well...
-No, no.

396
00:40:24,673 --> 00:40:26,341
Let's go light that roof back on fire.

397
00:40:26,633 --> 00:40:28,927
It was so easy
to put out the first time.

398
00:40:29,720 --> 00:40:30,721
(SIGHS)

399
00:40:31,180 --> 00:40:32,723
What are we talking about here?

400
00:40:34,808 --> 00:40:36,351
We need another robot.

401
00:40:37,853 --> 00:40:40,147
One that can withstand the radiation.

402
00:40:40,814 --> 00:40:42,774
I've asked. There is nothing.

403
00:40:44,276 --> 00:40:45,486
The Americans?

404
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:48,155
If the Americans had
that kind of technology,

405
00:40:48,238 --> 00:40:49,823
do you really think
they'd give it to us?

406
00:40:49,907 --> 00:40:50,908
And even if they would,

407
00:40:50,991 --> 00:40:52,451
the Central Committee
would never stoop to ask.

408
00:40:52,826 --> 00:40:54,161
You know it, I know it.

409
00:40:55,787 --> 00:40:56,997
There are no robots.

410
00:41:04,129 --> 00:41:05,214
LEGASOV: Biorobots.

411
00:41:06,548 --> 00:41:07,549
What was that?

412
00:41:09,468 --> 00:41:10,469
(CLEARS THROAT)

413
00:41:12,721 --> 00:41:15,891
We use biorobots.

414
00:41:19,061 --> 00:41:20,062
Men.

415
00:41:36,620 --> 00:41:37,621
(GUNSHOTS IN DISTANCE)

416
00:41:45,504 --> 00:41:47,631
(DOG BARKING)

417
00:41:56,598 --> 00:41:57,724
(GUN COCKS)

418
00:41:59,643 --> 00:42:00,936
(DOG BARKING)

419
00:42:04,815 --> 00:42:05,816
(GUNSHOT)

420
00:42:07,943 --> 00:42:08,944
(DOG BARKS)

421
00:42:10,195 --> 00:42:11,196
(GUN COCKING)

422
00:42:16,076 --> 00:42:17,077
(DOG SNARLING)

423
00:42:21,123 --> 00:42:22,124
(DOG WHIMPERING)

424
00:42:27,921 --> 00:42:28,922
(GUN FIRES IN DISTANCE)

425
00:42:48,942 --> 00:42:50,193
A lot today.

426
00:42:55,490 --> 00:42:56,867
Where do they get their food?

427
00:42:59,911 --> 00:43:01,079
BACHO: They eat the chickens.

428
00:43:02,748 --> 00:43:04,082
Then they eat each other.

429
00:43:14,968 --> 00:43:16,136
Door to door.

430
00:44:03,809 --> 00:44:04,810
(DOG YELPS)

431
00:44:06,019 --> 00:44:07,312
(WHIMPERING)

432
00:44:23,161 --> 00:44:24,162
(WHIMPERING CONTINUES)

433
00:44:25,831 --> 00:44:26,832
(SNARLING)

434
00:44:28,583 --> 00:44:29,584
BACHO: Pavel?

435
00:44:35,006 --> 00:44:36,007
Pavel

436
00:44:38,969 --> 00:44:40,971
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

437
00:44:45,142 --> 00:44:47,602
You don't hear me? I'm talking to you.

438
00:44:50,188 --> 00:44:51,189
Fuck.

439
00:44:56,695 --> 00:44:57,696
Just go outside.

440
00:44:58,488 --> 00:44:59,489
(PUPPIES YELPING)

441
00:45:04,786 --> 00:45:05,787
Go.

442
00:45:29,186 --> 00:45:30,187
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

443
00:45:37,277 --> 00:45:38,278
(GUN FIRING)

444
00:46:03,136 --> 00:46:04,137
(FIRING CONTINUES)

445
00:46:11,520 --> 00:46:12,521
(FIRING STOPS)

446
00:46:37,546 --> 00:46:39,548
(MAN SINGING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

447
00:47:59,753 --> 00:48:00,962
TARAKANOV: Comrade soldiers,

448
00:48:01,504 --> 00:48:03,965
the Soviet people have had
enough of this accident.

449
00:48:04,507 --> 00:48:05,926
They want us to clean it up,

450
00:48:06,009 --> 00:48:08,428
and we have entrusted you
with this serious task.

451
00:48:09,095 --> 00:48:10,555
Because of the nature
of the working area,

452
00:48:11,097 --> 00:48:14,476
you will each have no more
than 90 seconds to solve this problem.

453
00:48:15,143 --> 00:48:17,896
Listen carefully
to each of my instructions,

454
00:48:17,979 --> 00:48:20,565
and do exactly as you have been told.

455
00:48:20,649 --> 00:48:24,611
This is for your own safety
and the safety of your comrades.

456
00:48:25,362 --> 00:48:27,238
You will enter Reactor Building Three.

457
00:48:27,739 --> 00:48:31,368
Climb the stairs, but do not
immediately proceed to the roof.

458
00:48:31,451 --> 00:48:33,703
When you get to the top, wait inside,

459
00:48:33,787 --> 00:48:36,122
behind the entrance to the roof
and catch your breath.

460
00:48:36,665 --> 00:48:38,917
You will need it for what comes next.

461
00:48:39,334 --> 00:48:42,504
This is the working area.
We must clear the graphite.

462
00:48:42,587 --> 00:48:43,797
Some of it is in blocks,

463
00:48:43,880 --> 00:48:46,007
weighing approximately
40 to 50 kilograms.

464
00:48:46,091 --> 00:48:48,259
They all must be thrown
over the edge here.

465
00:48:48,677 --> 00:48:52,013
Watch your comrades
moving fast from this opening,

466
00:48:52,097 --> 00:48:55,684
then turning to the left,
and entering the workspace here.

467
00:48:56,059 --> 00:48:57,644
Take care not to stumble.

468
00:48:58,311 --> 00:49:00,313
There's a hole in the roof.
Take care not to fall.

469
00:49:01,731 --> 00:49:05,068
You will need to move quickly,
and you will need to move carefully.

470
00:49:06,319 --> 00:49:08,697
Do you understand your mission
as I have described it?

471
00:49:08,780 --> 00:49:10,448
ALL: Yes, Comrade General.

472
00:49:10,865 --> 00:49:13,910
These are the most important
90 seconds of your lives.

473
00:49:14,369 --> 00:49:17,580
Commit your task to memory,
then do your job.

474
00:49:42,105 --> 00:49:43,606
(CLANGING)

475
00:50:00,749 --> 00:50:03,626
It's time to go.
After 90 seconds, I will ring a bell.

476
00:50:03,793 --> 00:50:06,504
When you hear it, return immediately,
drop your shovels in the bin,

477
00:50:07,005 --> 00:50:09,382
and proceed down the hallway
for decontamination.

478
00:50:09,966 --> 00:50:13,136
Above all, while on the roof,
throw your debris over the rail.

479
00:50:13,219 --> 00:50:14,846
Do not look over the rail.
Is that clear?

480
00:50:16,222 --> 00:50:20,185
Very well. On my mark. Ready. Go.

481
00:50:23,938 --> 00:50:25,940
(RADIATION DETECTOR CRACKLING)

482
00:50:31,196 --> 00:50:33,198
(PANTING)

483
00:50:41,664 --> 00:50:43,666
(CRACKLING CONTINUES)

484
00:51:01,976 --> 00:51:03,978
(CRACKLING INTENSIFIES)

485
00:51:10,318 --> 00:51:12,320
(CRACKLING DECREASES)

486
00:51:13,530 --> 00:51:14,531
(GRUNTS)

487
00:51:23,498 --> 00:51:25,500
(CRACKLING INTENSIFIES)

488
00:51:27,627 --> 00:51:28,628
(GRUNTS)

489
00:51:28,711 --> 00:51:30,713
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

490
00:51:38,054 --> 00:51:40,056
(CRACKLING INTENSIFIES)

491
00:51:44,269 --> 00:51:46,271
(CRACKLING DECREASES)

492
00:51:52,235 --> 00:51:54,237
(LOUD CLANGING)

493
00:51:59,701 --> 00:52:01,536
<i>Whoa!</i>

494
00:52:03,830 --> 00:52:05,832
(CRACKLING INTENSIFIES)

495
00:52:06,833 --> 00:52:07,834
(CLANGING CONTINUES)

496
00:52:09,127 --> 00:52:11,129
(GRUNTING)

497
00:52:25,935 --> 00:52:27,937
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

498
00:52:33,193 --> 00:52:34,194
Comrade soldier.

499
00:52:36,070 --> 00:52:37,071
You're done.

500
00:52:41,201 --> 00:52:42,535
(DEVICE CRACKLING)

501
00:52:48,458 --> 00:52:49,459
(SIGHS)

502
00:52:49,542 --> 00:52:50,627
Time to go.

503
00:52:51,753 --> 00:52:53,755
(CHILDREN CHATTERING)

504
00:53:03,765 --> 00:53:05,350
Oil Your glove!

505
00:53:09,187 --> 00:53:10,188
(GASPS)

506
00:53:11,981 --> 00:53:12,982
(GROANS)

507
00:53:15,318 --> 00:53:17,028
(GROANING)

508
00:53:20,490 --> 00:53:22,367
(SCREAMS)

509
00:53:26,120 --> 00:53:27,288
Mommy! Mommy!

510
00:53:35,838 --> 00:53:36,839
(INAUDIBLE)

511
00:54:32,145 --> 00:54:33,313
SHCHERBINA: Sorry for all this.

512
00:54:34,564 --> 00:54:36,941
But we needed to speak to you
somewhere without...

513
00:54:38,693 --> 00:54:40,653
LEGASOV: They're going to put
Dyatlov on trial,

514
00:54:41,571 --> 00:54:43,364
and Bryukhanov and Fomin.

515
00:54:43,698 --> 00:54:47,285
We're going to be asked
to give expert testimony,

516
00:54:47,493 --> 00:54:48,578
all three of us.

517
00:54:49,162 --> 00:54:50,163
But that's...

518
00:54:50,496 --> 00:54:51,539
Before that happens...

519
00:54:51,914 --> 00:54:55,251
The Central Committee
is sending Legasov to Vienna.

520
00:54:55,335 --> 00:54:57,337
It's the headquarters
of the International Atomic...

521
00:54:57,420 --> 00:55:00,423
Atomic Energy Agency.
Yeah, I know what's in Vienna.

522
00:55:02,550 --> 00:55:04,218
What are they asking you to do?

523
00:55:05,011 --> 00:55:06,471
Tell the world what happened.

524
00:55:12,018 --> 00:55:13,478
Well, then you'd better
know what happened.

525
00:55:14,354 --> 00:55:17,440
I've constructed a timeline,
minute by minute.

526
00:55:18,441 --> 00:55:20,276
Second by second in some places.

527
00:55:21,361 --> 00:55:24,530
Every decision, every button push,
every turn of a switch.

528
00:55:25,281 --> 00:55:27,283
And? Are they guilty?

529
00:55:28,159 --> 00:55:29,160
Yes.

530
00:55:30,119 --> 00:55:33,664
Of gross incompetence,
violation of safety regulations,

531
00:55:33,748 --> 00:55:35,375
recklessness beyond belief.

532
00:55:36,042 --> 00:55:38,628
But the explosion? I'm not sure.

533
00:55:38,836 --> 00:55:40,296
What do you mean, you're not sure?

534
00:55:41,756 --> 00:55:43,383
I've analyzed the data.

535
00:55:44,050 --> 00:55:45,802
Toptunov was telling the truth.

536
00:55:46,469 --> 00:55:49,305
They shut the reactor down,
and then it exploded.

537
00:55:51,057 --> 00:55:53,518
I think
this article may have the answer,

538
00:55:54,519 --> 00:55:56,938
but two pages have been removed.

539
00:56:03,444 --> 00:56:04,862
You've seen this before.

540
00:56:05,530 --> 00:56:08,116
Please, believe me when I tell you

541
00:56:08,324 --> 00:56:10,701
that I had no idea
it could cause an explosion.

542
00:56:10,785 --> 00:56:13,788
-None of us knew.
-None of you knew what?

543
00:56:15,164 --> 00:56:18,042
In 1975, at an RBMK reactor
in Leningrad,

544
00:56:18,584 --> 00:56:22,380
a fuel channel ruptured.
The operators pressed AZ-5,

545
00:56:22,463 --> 00:56:24,966
but instead of the power
going down immediately,

546
00:56:25,341 --> 00:56:28,010
for a brief moment, it went up.

547
00:56:28,719 --> 00:56:30,012
How is that possible?

548
00:56:30,096 --> 00:56:33,558
Well, this was the very question posed
by a colleague of mine named Volkov.

549
00:56:33,641 --> 00:56:35,143
He's the one who wrote this article.

550
00:56:35,810 --> 00:56:37,728
When an RBMK reactor runs
at low power,

551
00:56:37,812 --> 00:56:39,439
it's notoriously unstable.

552
00:56:39,605 --> 00:56:41,607
Prone to swings in reactivity.

553
00:56:42,817 --> 00:56:44,986
Under normal circumstances,
the control rods

554
00:56:45,069 --> 00:56:47,572
-can compensate for that.
-Under normal circumstances.

555
00:56:47,655 --> 00:56:51,075
The Chernobyl staff stalled
the reactor during the test.

556
00:56:51,492 --> 00:56:53,161
They pulled
almost all the control rods out

557
00:56:53,244 --> 00:56:54,287
to bring the power back up.

558
00:56:54,370 --> 00:56:56,789
This is what Volkov learned
from Leningrad.

559
00:56:57,165 --> 00:57:00,001
If the boron control rods
are completely withdrawn

560
00:57:00,084 --> 00:57:02,503
from the reactor,
when they're put back in,

561
00:57:02,587 --> 00:57:05,882
the first thing
that enters the core isn't boron.

562
00:57:06,674 --> 00:57:07,925
It's graphite.

563
00:57:11,387 --> 00:57:15,558
The control rods have graphite tips
that displace water and steam.

564
00:57:16,184 --> 00:57:20,229
So the reactivity doesn't go down.
It goes up dramatically.

565
00:57:20,646 --> 00:57:21,647
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

566
00:57:21,731 --> 00:57:24,066
Why on earth
would they press that button?

567
00:57:24,609 --> 00:57:25,776
They didn't know.

568
00:57:28,112 --> 00:57:29,739
LEGASOV: Volkov warned the Kremlin,

569
00:57:30,740 --> 00:57:31,824
10 years ago.

570
00:57:32,992 --> 00:57:33,993
(SIGHS)

571
00:57:34,076 --> 00:57:37,622
But there could be no doubt
about the supremacy

572
00:57:37,705 --> 00:57:39,790
of the Soviet nuclear industry.

573
00:57:40,500 --> 00:57:41,501
Oh.

574
00:57:41,834 --> 00:57:45,046
The KGB classified it
as a state secret.

575
00:57:47,757 --> 00:57:49,133
LEGASOV: When I saw
the reactor blown open,

576
00:57:49,217 --> 00:57:52,053
I still didn't think
it could be this flaw in AZ-5.

577
00:57:52,887 --> 00:57:56,057
Because the flaw will not lead
to an explosion

578
00:57:56,307 --> 00:58:00,937
unless the operators have pushed
the reactor to the edge of disaster.

579
00:58:01,270 --> 00:58:03,356
-So it is their fault?
-Yes.

580
00:58:04,106 --> 00:58:05,525
KHOMYUK: But not only their fault.

581
00:58:07,485 --> 00:58:08,486
No.

582
00:58:10,238 --> 00:58:12,240
Is that
what you're going to say in Vienna?

583
00:58:16,244 --> 00:58:18,496
You can't possibly be that naive.

584
00:58:19,330 --> 00:58:25,044
There are 16 RBMK reactors
running in the Soviet Union right now.

585
00:58:25,127 --> 00:58:26,712
We have to fix them.

586
00:58:27,213 --> 00:58:30,007
The only way to do that
is to go public,

587
00:58:30,174 --> 00:58:32,134
force the Central Committee
to take action.

588
00:58:32,218 --> 00:58:35,137
What you're proposing
is that Legasov humiliate a nation

589
00:58:35,221 --> 00:58:38,140
that is obsessed
with not being humiliated.

590
00:58:38,266 --> 00:58:39,976
We can make a deal with the KGB.

591
00:58:40,851 --> 00:58:43,020
You'll leave this information out
in Vienna,

592
00:58:43,187 --> 00:58:45,982
and they quietly
let us fix the remaining reactors.

593
00:58:46,065 --> 00:58:49,652
A deal with the KGB? And I'm naive.

594
00:58:51,696 --> 00:58:55,116
They'll go after your family,
they'll go after your friends.

595
00:58:55,199 --> 00:58:57,743
KHOMYUK: You have a chance
to talk to the world, Valery.

596
00:58:58,035 --> 00:58:59,912
If that chance was mine...

597
00:58:59,996 --> 00:59:01,247
But it isn't, is it?

598
00:59:02,957 --> 00:59:05,334
I've known braver souls
than you, Khomyuk.

599
00:59:06,127 --> 00:59:08,129
Men who had their moment
and did nothing.

600
00:59:08,379 --> 00:59:11,465
Because when it's your life
and the lives of everyone you love,

601
00:59:12,633 --> 00:59:14,677
your moral conviction
doesn't mean anything.

602
00:59:15,136 --> 00:59:16,262
It leaves you.

603
00:59:17,638 --> 00:59:21,350
And all you want at that moment
is not to be shot.

604
00:59:26,105 --> 00:59:28,399
Do you know the name VASILY Ignatenko?

605
00:59:29,317 --> 00:59:30,318
No.

606
00:59:31,235 --> 00:59:32,486
He was a fireman.

607
00:59:34,238 --> 00:59:36,407
He died two weeks after the accident.

608
00:59:37,491 --> 00:59:39,076
I've been looking in on his widow.

609
00:59:40,328 --> 00:59:42,663
She gave birth. A girl.

610
00:59:43,706 --> 00:59:45,458
The baby lived for four hours.

611
00:59:47,251 --> 00:59:48,919
They said the radiation
would have killed the mother,

612
00:59:49,003 --> 00:59:50,838
but the baby absorbed it instead.

613
00:59:51,756 --> 00:59:52,757
Her baby.

614
00:59:55,009 --> 00:59:56,135
We live in a country

615
00:59:56,469 --> 00:59:58,888
where children have to die
to save their mothers.

616
01:00:00,348 --> 01:00:01,390
To hell with your deal.

617
01:00:04,518 --> 01:00:05,895
And to hell with our lives.

618
01:00:08,564 --> 01:00:10,232
Someone has to start
telling the truth.

619
01:00:25,039 --> 01:00:26,791
TARAKANOV: Congratulations, comrades.

620
01:00:27,458 --> 01:00:30,878
You are the last of 3,828 men.

621
01:00:31,379 --> 01:00:33,714
You have performed
your duties perfectly.

622
01:00:33,798 --> 01:00:36,050
I wish you good health and long life.

623
01:00:36,300 --> 01:00:39,178
All of you are awarded
a bonus of 800 rubles.

624
01:00:39,345 --> 01:00:40,930
-Thank you.
-1 serve the Soviet Union.

625
01:00:41,013 --> 01:00:42,848
-Thank you.
-1 serve the Soviet Union.

626
01:00:42,932 --> 01:00:44,684
-Thank you.
-1 serve the Soviet Union.

627
01:00:44,767 --> 01:00:46,394
-Thank you.
-1 serve the Soviet Union.

628
01:00:46,477 --> 01:00:48,437
-Thank you.
-1 serve the Soviet Union.

629
01:00:48,521 --> 01:00:50,189
-Thank you.
-1 serve the Soviet Union.

630
01:00:50,272 --> 01:00:51,816
-Thank you.
-1 serve the Soviet Union.

631
01:00:51,899 --> 01:00:53,234
-Thank you.
-1 serve the Soviet Union.

632
01:00:53,317 --> 01:00:55,277
-Thank you.
-1 serve the Soviet Union.

633
01:01:29,603 --> 01:01:31,063
(BABIES CRYING)

